cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortTable
cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortTable.description: This table contains TCOP Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTTCOPPortEntry.description: Each PortEntry contains the configuration parameters for one TCOP port.

cdx6500TCOPCfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgPortNumber
cdx6500TCOPCfgPortNumber.description: Port number of the port being used by TCOP.

cdx6500TCOPCfgSubtype.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgSubtype
cdx6500TCOPCfgSubtype.description: Select the sub-type for the synchronous protocol running on this port. hsc3 - Transparent Hitachi type gnet - Transparent GNET type. uts - Transparent Uniscope type. slc - Synchronous Link Control. ac100 - AC100.

cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSource.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSource
cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSource.description: int - internal clock source ext - external clock source on pins 18 and 24.

cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSpeed.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSpeed
cdx6500TCOPCfgClockSpeed.description: This is the port speed in bits per second, when clock source = int.

cdx6500TCOPCfgContention.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgContention
cdx6500TCOPCfgContention.description: Specifies the line contention. hdx - Half duplex, DCD toggles fdx - Full duplex, DCD is always high.

cdx6500TCOPCfgCodeType.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgCodeType
cdx6500TCOPCfgCodeType.description: Either of ascii or ebcdic code set is used.

cdx6500TCOPCfgReceiveByteCount.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgReceiveByteCount
cdx6500TCOPCfgReceiveByteCount.description: Specifies the number of bytes collected from the line before data is forwarded to the network. A minimum byte count constraint is imposed for port speed intervals as shown in the following pairs of (port speed in bps, minimum byte count): (19200 to 80000, 127); (9600 to 19200, 64); (4800 to 9600, 32); (2400 to 4800, 16); (below 2400, 8).

cdx6500TCOPCfgCallControl.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgCallControl
cdx6500TCOPCfgCallControl.description: none - port will generate a call auto - Autocalling enabled.

cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallMnem.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallMnem
cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallMnem.description: This mnemonic name is used for Auto calling.

cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallTO.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallTO
cdx6500TCOPCfgAutoCallTO.description: Specifies the time in seconds between call attempts when autocalling.

cdx6500TCOPCfgMaxAutoCallTries.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgMaxAutoCallTries
cdx6500TCOPCfgMaxAutoCallTries.description: Specifies the maximum number of times the TCOP port will attempt to call. A value of 0 will allow unlimited number of attempts.

cdx6500TCOPCfgPortAddress.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgPortAddress
cdx6500TCOPCfgPortAddress.description: The BCD address specified here is inserted in the calling address field when the TCOP port makes a call.

cdx6500TCOPCfgProtocolID.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgProtocolID
cdx6500TCOPCfgProtocolID.description: The protocol identifier specified here is inserted into a call packet or checked against the identifier of an incoming call.

cdx6500TCOPCfgEnableBill.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgEnableBill
cdx6500TCOPCfgEnableBill.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this TCOP port.

cdx6500TCOPCfgRestrictConn.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgRestrictConn
cdx6500TCOPCfgRestrictConn.description: Specifies the destination of all calls routed to from this port, regardless of route selection table entries. For example, to route calls to port 1, use P1. To route calls to port 2, station 4, use P2S4. To route call to X25 port 2, enter X25-2. Blank this field to disable this functionality.

cdx6500TCOPCfgRXQueue.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgRXQueue
cdx6500TCOPCfgRXQueue.description: Specifies the maximum number of received messages to be queued. This parameter is effective only when sub-type = gnet.

cdx6500TCOPCfgTXQueue.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgTXQueue
cdx6500TCOPCfgTXQueue.description: Specifies the maximum number of transmit messages to be queued. This parameter is effective only when sub-type = gnet.

cdx6500TCOPCfgQueueOverflow.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgQueueOverflow
cdx6500TCOPCfgQueueOverflow.description: Specifies the action to be taken if the receive message queue overflows. This parameter is effective only when sub-type = gnet. resetConnection - Reset connections dropMessage - Drop the message causing overflow flushQueue - Flush the queue eotMessage - Flush the queue when receiving message terminated with EOT.

cdx6500TCOPCfgPortType.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgPortType
cdx6500TCOPCfgPortType.description: The Port Type of the port.

cdx6500TCOPCfgDataTransmission.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgDataTransmission
cdx6500TCOPCfgDataTransmission.description: This determines the mode of data transfer. hdx - Indicates half duplex data transfer. fdx - Indicates full duplex data transfer.

cdx6500TCOPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500TCOPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500TCOPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500TCOPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500TCOPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.name: cdx6500TCOPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500TCOPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortTable
cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortTable.description: This table holds statistics items for TCOP ports.

cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTTCOPPortEntry.description: This entry holds the statistics items for one TCOP port.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortNumber.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortNumber
cdx6500TCOPStatPortNumber.description: The port number for this TCOP entry.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortType.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortType
cdx6500TCOPStatPortType.description: The configured value of the Port Type.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortSubtype.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortSubtype
cdx6500TCOPStatPortSubtype.description: Access protocol for this port. hsc3 - Transparent Hitachi type gnet - Transparent GNET type. uts - Transparent Uniscope type. slc - Synchronous Link Control. ac100 - AC100.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortStatus.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortStatus
cdx6500TCOPStatPortStatus.description: Status of this port: Up : Port is enabled Down : Port is Inactive Disabled : Port is disabled.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortState.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortState
cdx6500TCOPStatPortState.description: Current port state: discPhase - Disconnect phase, no call in place callingPhase - Port has initiated Autocall calledPhase - Port has received a call request connected - Connection has been established.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortSpeed.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortSpeed
cdx6500TCOPStatPortSpeed.description: The measured port speed in bits per second.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilIn.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilIn
cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilIn.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilOut.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilOut
cdx6500TCOPStatPortUtilOut.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOverrunErrs.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOverrunErrs
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOverrunErrs.description: Total number of overrun errors counted by the I/O driver since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortUnderrunErrs.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortUnderrunErrs
cdx6500TCOPStatPortUnderrunErrs.description: Total number of underrun errors counted by the I/O driver since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortBCCErrs.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortBCCErrs

cdx6500TCOPStatPortParityErrs.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortParityErrs
cdx6500TCOPStatPortParityErrs.description: Total number of parity errors counted by the I/O driver since the last node or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortInChars.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortInChars
cdx6500TCOPStatPortInChars.description: Number of characters received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutChars.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutChars
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutChars.description: Number of characters sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortInCharsRate.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortInCharsRate
cdx6500TCOPStatPortInCharsRate.description: Average number of characters received per second since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutCharsRate.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutCharsRate
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutCharsRate.description: Average number of characters sent per second since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessages.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessages
cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessages.description: Number of messages received since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessages.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessages
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessages.description: Number of messages sent since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessagesRate.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessagesRate
cdx6500TCOPStatPortInMessagesRate.description: Average number of messages received per second since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessagesRate.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessagesRate
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutMessagesRate.description: Average number of messages sent per second since last node, port or statistics reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortInPktsQueued.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortInPktsQueued
cdx6500TCOPStatPortInPktsQueued.description: Number of received packets which are currently queued.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutPktsQueued.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutPktsQueued
cdx6500TCOPStatPortOutPktsQueued.description: Number of packets currently queued which are to be sent.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxInQueueLength.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxInQueueLength
cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxInQueueLength.description: The maximum queue length reached for incoming packets since the last reset.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxOutQueueLength.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxOutQueueLength
cdx6500TCOPStatPortMaxOutQueueLength.description: The maximum queue length reached since the last reset, for packets to be sent.

cdx6500TCOPStatPortPktQueueFlushCount.name: cdx6500TCOPStatPortPktQueueFlushCount
cdx6500TCOPStatPortPktQueueFlushCount.description: The number of times the receive queue is flushed.

cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallNextAttempt.name: cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallNextAttempt
cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallNextAttempt.description: Time in seconds until next autocall attempt.

cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearCause.name: cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearCause
cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearCause.description: Last autocall clear cause code dte - Cleared by other end np - Destination not obtainable occ - Called number busy nc - Network congested inv - Invalid facility requested na - Access barred err - Local procedure error rpe - Remote procedure error der - Called number out of order rna - Reverse charging not accepted roo - RPOA out of order icd - Incompatible destination fsn - Fast select acceptance not subscribed ctp - Control port intervention sha - Ship absent.

cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearDiagnosi.name: cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearDiagnosis
cdx6500TCOPStatAutoCallLastClearDiagnosi.description: Last clear diagnostic code none - No more information bps - Invalid P(S) bpr - Invalid P(R) ptinv - Packet type invalid pna - Packet not allowed psh - Packet too short pln - Packet too long tout - Timer expired tcli - Timer expired for clear indication nocs - Call set-up problem nofc - Facility/registration code not allowed nofp - Facility/registration parameter not allowed cald - Bad called address cali - Bad calling address invfl - Invalid facilities length icb - Incoming call barred nolcn - No logical channel available cco - Call collision occurred dupl - Duplicate facility requested nadl - Non-zero address length nfcl - Non-zero facility length nfce - Facility not found when expected trp - Temporary routing problem clin - Call limit reached on intermediate node cldn - Call limit reached on destination node ncil - No logical channel available on internode link ccpo - Call cleared by Control Port operator csld - Call setup looping detected cshe - Call setup hop count exceeded finl - Failure on intermediate node link rin3 - Restart received at level 3 disc - DISC received at level 2 dm - DM received at level 2 sabm - SABM received at level 2 frmr - FRMR received at level 2 invnr - Invalid N(R) unsf - Unsolicited F bit received ucmd - Unknown command received uresp - Unknown response received gtcap - I field too long t1to - T1/N2 timeout frlen - Received frame of incorrect size aderr - Address error spbo - Source port is in Busy Out state dpbo - Destination port is in Busy Out state srr - Session reconnection rejected.
